I'm surprised and dismayed that Jira has no built-in support for a per-component default QA contact, with automatic assignment at issue creation, a huge lacuna in a tool that bills itself as a "bug and issue tracker."  I'm sure this request has been filed many times, but a quick search didn't turn up anything obvious.  I found the following thread on the web:

http://osdir.com/ml/java.jira.user/2004-11/msg00338.html

But the comments by the Jira person are vague, at best, and a specific workaround example would really be appreciated.  I've been involved in QA for almost 20 years and in that time I've never been at a company, large or small, whose bug tracking tool didn't support default QA contact by component (or similar notion).  If there is a Jira workaround for such a feature can it be linked to this report?

The Manage Project Role Membership for Project page has a mistranslation:

{quote}
The page that ist found under "Administration => Projekt => View mebers", is called "Manage Project Role Membership for Project:" in English.

In German, this page is titled "Regeln bearbeiten", which means "Edit Rules". I suppose it should be "Rollen bearbeiten", which means "Edit Roles".
{quote}

